    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've created:\n\n## Plan: Add `ollama rename` Feature\n\nThe implementation touches **4 files**, all following exact patterns already present in the codebase:\n\n---\n\n### `api/types.go`\nAdd `RenameRequest` struct — identical shape to `CopyRequest` (two `string` fields: `source`, `destination`).\n\n### `api/client.go`\nAdd `Client.Rename()` — identical to `Client.Copy()`, calls `c.do(ctx, http.MethodPost, \"/api/rename\", req, nil)`.\n\n### `server/routes.go` (two changes)\n1. **`RenameHandler` method** — blends `CopyHandler` (for validation + `CopyModel`) and `DeleteHandler` (for `m.Remove()` + `m.RemoveLayers()`):\n   - Validates non-empty fields → 400\n   - Validates names with `model.ParseName()` + `IsValid()` → 400 + `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n   - Qualifies names with `getExistingName()` (same as `CopyHandler`)\n   - Checks destination exists via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409 Conflict** if found\n   - Calls `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 if src missing\n   - Deletes source via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()`\n   - Returns 200 `{\"status\": \"success\"}`\n2. **Route registration**: `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after `/api/copy`\n\n**No new imports needed** — all packages already imported in `routes.go`.\n\n### `cmd/cmd.go` (three changes)\n1. `RenameHandler` function — mirrors `CopyHandler`, prints `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"`\n2. `renameCmd` cobra command — `rename SOURCE DESTINATION`, `ExactArgs(2)`, `PreRunE: checkServerHeartbeat`\n3. Register `renameCmd` in both the env-docs loop and `rootCmd.AddCommand()`, placed after `copyCmd`",
